article.headline: Alcorn State 75, Grambling 71
article.story: GRAMBLING, La. (AP) -- Delvin Thompson had 21 points to lead Alcorn State to a 75-71 victory over Grambling State on Monday night. Clif Douglass had 18 points, Juan Wyatt added 16 points and Jarvis Williams finished with 13 for the Braves (5-15, 5-6 Southwestern Athletic Conference), who won despite being shorthanded. Forwards Almaad Jackson and James Kendrick and guard Carl Landry were injured and missed the game. Alcorn State scored 10 straight points in the second half and led 72-63 with 4:31 to play, and Thompson was 3-of-4 from the free-throw line in the closing moments to preserve the victory.
